JAGS (Just Another Gibbs Sampler) is a program for analysis of Bayesian hierarchical models using Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) simulation not wholly unlike BUGS. <br /><br />'''Useful Links:'''

* JAGS documentation is available on the [http://mcmc-jags.sourceforge.net/ JAGS website]    <br /><br />
==Setup==
<br />Use:
<code>
 module unload compilers
 module load compilers/gnu/4.9.2
 module load atlas/3.10.2/gnu-4.9.2
 module load jags/3.4.0/gnu.4.9.2-atlas
</code>
to use JAGS in standalone command line mode.

We have also added JAGS support to our recommended version of R using the <code>rjags</code> and <code>R2jags</code> R packages. See the [[R packages available on Legion]] page.







